column5: Anybody ever try/succeed on lake trout in LS? There are some deep water areas west of Taylor I a few miles that I've seen on a map, just wondering if anyone has ever actually boated any in the area.
Unless I just had a lot of time to waste, I wouldn't waste my time even trying to catch a lake trout on LS.
Just thinking about alternatives in the event the walleye water goes board flat and the wind dies, or if we're on the way to somewhere else. I would not specifically dedicate a day to it.
Lodge owners on Lac Seul have told me the same thing over the years we have fished that lake: There was a population of Lake Trout, but were netted out years ago.
There are some lakers in there...see this report:http://www.sww-lodge.com/?s=Lake+troutFrank
